The paper focuses on the task of Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates the robustness of VQA models, which can be considered a form of machine learning, falling under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions the use of large-scale datasets, which can be related to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
